main event: A civilian graduate student observed a pulsating object shaped like a star with a dull-red light trailing behind it on September 29, 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 15 to 20 seconds,The object was moving at an estimated speed three times faster than a jet,There was no sound emitted from the object,The object had no discernible features and left no trail,The sighting occurred over the University of Illinois campus at night.
sighted object: a pulsating star-shaped object with a dull-red light
witness description: Civilian graduate student in Civil Engineering at the University of Illinois
